		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				Unfortunately, you can't copyright an idea. You need to have something in a tangible form in order to get a copyright for it. The best I could do is try and get some investors to put up the money, but as good as this idea may sound to you, getting people to put up the money for it, is a daunting task. It's like anything else, you may have a great idea for a movie that will be a blockbuster hit, but if you are just a plumber in Arkansas, nobody is going to listen to you. The first thing an investor will ask me is how much experience do I have designing video games. The answer is none except for a few BASIC games I wrote for my Commodore 64. Then they would show me out the door. <br>  <br> I think a game like this will eventually be made. I'm sure I'm not the only one perceptive enough to see what the MMORPG industry is lacking. We just need the right person in the right place. Of course if anyone out there has a few extra million lying around, I'd be happy to lend a hand in getting this game off the ground.
