			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				While eating lunch, I was thinking of a lot of ideas for this Perfect MMORPG... one of the better ones fits the Explorer: Allow Character points to be obtained by exploring. Make invisible zone lines like in DAoC but have a formula so if you walk 1000 spaces in Temple of Doom in 10 minutes, you get (spaces)/(time)+50 rounded down, or something similar. Make it so the spaces have to be unique, as in you can't hit back then forward over and over, and make it so the timer for how long you've been &quot;exploring&quot; is only active while moving, that way you can't stand in one spot for a long time. The only problem with dividing is if you had a huge zone, the explorer would probably spend a long time looking around, which uses up a lot of time, but then again you would also be walking, which evens it out. Maybe even give the explorer some &quot;class skills&quot; like Map Making.
